Dahi is a yogurt-based soup that can be made with a variety of ingredients, whereas ham is a type of meat that can be served in many different ways. Dahi is a great substitute for curd made from milk, while ham is often used in popular dishes like rice and macs. With a healthy mix of healthy fats, protein, and vegetables, they are both a great food item that I am thankful to be able to have access to, and I especially like it with the type of bread that Daniel made. I love to make dahi at home when I have time, and I really appreciate that Daniel and his wife love to makes ham as well. I am grateful for having the opportunity to learn new recipes, and learn the process of how to make them, with fruit de mouton, ghee and masalas. I find the process very relaxing, especially if I have a lot in the kitchen, and I can remember the experts wouldn’t have a lot in the fridge. Egg in general is a great way to add proteins to my creative meals, with butter and garlic. I have had too many cooking inspirations for me to keep sharing with Daniel and allow him to have a good meal while at home with his daughter. For me it’s a creative style of learning and experimentation, and something that I can share with more of my family and friends. Countless types of food I didn’t even know existed are being introduced to me, with so much more to learn and prepare for my family, and I am grateful to all those foodie experiences I have had. They are endless, and I can count myself very lucky to have all these experiences to continue learning. Finally, one day I might tell my daughter her mother made the best tandoori chicken and bring into our house. I have had cooked and cooked a lot of delightful foods with room for more to come. I am thankful to have learned so much about cooking, thanks to all the recipes I have learned and have experimented with over the years. I have had a blast cooking for others, and am so happy to have had the opportunity to learn so many techniques, as I pass down dahi, my pies, and my bread. And lastly, I am thankful to learn from all the love and support that family can provide a little girl who truly loves putting together passionate dishes at home.
